es may seem ideal for portion control, but willpower is necessary to eat only one! They can be made ahead, brought to a picnic, offered as a gift, frozen for later, adapted to individual tastes…a great recipe to have up your sleeve.<\/i>","Once thoroughly chilled, cheesecakes may be frozen for serving later.<br>- Instead of jars use small heatproof drinking glasses or coffee cups.","Add flavourings to the filling (e.g. zest from one lemon or lime, <b>½ tsp ground<b> cinnamon).<br>- For a nut-free version, omit nuts and use <b>60 g biscuits.<b><br>- For a lighter version, omit crumb base.<br>- Instead of cooked berries, top with fresh seasonal fruit, caramel sauce or chocolate ganache."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","4h","6 jars"]}